cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.NI, cs.CY 

This paper primarily deals with the security aspects of Bitcoin, specifically the analysis of double-spending attacks based on hashrate. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Other likely categories include cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
